===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|ojp|jpx-pro|*sakai}}. Standalone form of ''saka-'' below.

Various theories exist regarding the ultimate derivation:
* Might be cognate with {{m|ojp||榮𛀁|tr=sakaye}}, the {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei||stem or continuative form}} of verb {{m|ojp|榮ゆ|tr=sakayu||to [[flourish]]}}.
* Might be derived from {{m|ojp|避く|tr=saku|t=to ward off, to shun}}, from the idea that drinking ''sake'' would ward off cold diseases.
* The final ''-ke<sub>2</sub>'' may be the [[apophony|apophonic]] form of {{m|ojp|酒|tr=ki<sub>1</sub>}}.

